with all the cousins and everyone?

295
00:25:30,737 --> 00:25:32,239
Uncle Eddie, see,

296
00:25:32,322 --> 00:25:35,617
he says that he has a place
that we can stay in for now, just us.

297
00:25:36,910 --> 00:25:37,911
It's gonna be good.

298
00:25:42,415 --> 00:25:43,415
Come on.

299
00:25:52,467 --> 00:25:53,677
I know it looks bad…

300
00:25:55,428 --> 00:25:56,428
but…

301
00:25:57,347 --> 00:25:59,474
we can, you know, the tires will go.

302
00:26:01,142 --> 00:26:02,143
No.

303
00:26:03,853 --> 00:26:05,730
I mean, if we just
move some things around...

304
00:26:05,814 --> 00:26:06,815
Abraham!

305
00:26:07,607 --> 00:26:08,733
No.

306
00:26:15,031 --> 00:26:16,032
Sorry.

307
00:26:25,292 --> 00:26:26,585
You guys need anything?

308
00:26:29,504 --> 00:26:31,047
No, brother, we're good.

309
00:26:32,299 --> 00:26:34,759
- Good night, then.
- Good night, Hector.

310
00:26:35,802 --> 00:26:37,002
Good night, Marcella.

311
00:26:37,846 --> 00:26:38,847
Good night, kids.

312
00:26:39,514 --> 00:26:41,266
Good night.

313
00:26:42,017 --> 00:26:43,018
Good night.

314
00:27:01,286 --> 00:27:02,537
All that skill…

315
00:27:03,455 --> 00:27:05,874
could be put to some use.

316
00:27:06,833 --> 00:27:07,834
It is.

317
00:27:09,085 --> 00:27:12,088
I'm making something
to carry our equipment.

318
00:27:12,172 --> 00:27:13,173
For the band.

319
00:27:13,757 --> 00:27:15,175
For the band.

320
00:27:17,761 --> 00:27:20,221
Eddie says he might need someone
to drive a truck.

321
00:27:20,305 --> 00:27:22,807
I'll drive a truck, sure.

322
00:27:23,725 --> 00:27:26,353
As long as it doesn't interfere.

323
00:27:27,896 --> 00:27:29,230
With the band.

324
00:27:29,898 --> 00:27:30,899
With the band.

325
00:27:33,860 --> 00:27:34,861
You haven't changed.

326
00:27:37,530 --> 00:27:39,407
Hector…

327
00:27:39,491 --> 00:27:40,867
<i>…</i>you wouldn't understand.

328
00:27:42,202 --> 00:27:43,328
I know, your music.

329
00:27:48,124 --> 00:27:49,793
Have you heard her, brother?

330
00:27:52,754 --> 00:27:53,880
My Selena can sing.

331
00:27:55,965 --> 00:27:58,718
I drive a truck. I drive another truck.
I drive another truck.

332
00:27:58,802 --> 00:28:00,804
In ten years, I'm still driving a truck,

333
00:28:00,887 --> 00:28:02,389
or in ten years, she's a star.

334
00:28:04,432 --> 00:28:05,432
She's not me.

335
00:28:07,060 --> 00:28:08,061
She's going places.

336
00:28:08,728 --> 00:28:11,314
- In a homemade trailer.
- In whatever it takes!

337
00:28:23,284 --> 00:28:25,704
You remember Ozzie? Hmm?

338
00:28:28,581 --> 00:28:30,166
His daughter's getting married.

339
00:28:31,668 --> 00:28:32,836
Maybe talk to him.

340
00:28:46,224 --> 00:28:47,392
I just got back.

341
00:28:47,475 --> 00:28:49,936
I saw Hector, and he said
that your Sofia's getting married.

342
00:28:50,019 --> 00:28:51,980
- How's that even possible?
- I know, right?

343
00:28:52,063 --> 00:28:54,023
It goes by so fast.

344
00:28:54,107 --> 00:28:55,275
Congratulations.

345
00:28:55,900 --> 00:28:57,527
Thank you.

346
00:28:57,610 --> 00:29:00,947
Hey, so, for the party after.
You have a band yet?

347
00:29:02,073 --> 00:29:03,992
Nah, bands are expensive.

348
00:29:05,034 --> 00:29:07,162
- We got a DJ.
- A DJ.

349
00:29:07,245 --> 00:29:08,955
No, no, no, no, no, no.

350
00:29:09,038 --> 00:29:12,459
Sofia deserves a band.
I tell you what, let me do it for you.

351
00:29:12,542 --> 00:29:16,546
Not much more than a DJ,
plus we play Tejano music, pop…

352
00:29:16,629 --> 00:29:18,673
whatever keeps your guests
dancing all night.

353
00:29:19,632 --> 00:29:20,672
It's just in the backyard.

354
00:29:20,717 --> 00:29:23,636
We don't have lights or sound.
The DJ was bringing all that.

355
00:29:23,720 --> 00:29:24,929
Not a problem.

356
00:29:25,013 --> 00:29:27,182
We have it all.
Lights, sound… lots of lights.

357
00:29:27,265 --> 00:29:28,266
Don't worry.

358
00:29:28,349 --> 00:29:30,059
We got you, huh?

359
00:29:30,143 --> 00:29:32,145
Sit down,
like when we were kids.

360
00:29:53,917 --> 00:29:55,877
Hey. Come with me.

361
00:29:56,961 --> 00:29:59,798
- Where?
- To get some lights. Come on.

362
00:30:22,946 --> 00:30:26,866
New lights. This is what I've been saying.
We need to step up.

363
00:30:27,534 --> 00:30:29,577
Get a real lighting package
with a dimmer board,

364
00:30:29,661 --> 00:30:30,745
so we look professional.

365
00:30:31,329 --> 00:30:34,707
Plus, bigger amps, bigger speakers,
so we can play at bigger places.

366
00:30:40,338 --> 00:30:42,465
So, how far are we going for these lights?

367
00:30:44,092 --> 00:30:45,093
Not far.

368
00:30:48,763 --> 00:30:50,014
Where are we going?

369
00:30:51,766 --> 00:30:52,934
Why are we at Luby's?

370
00:30:53,476 --> 00:30:55,562
Ah. We're gonna eat first.

371
00:30:58,064 --> 00:31:01,067
- Peach cans?
- Number four and number nine peach cans.

372
00:31:01,150 --> 00:31:02,235
Perfect sizes.

373
00:31:04,028 --> 00:31:05,738
You said we were buying lights.

374
00:31:06,239 --> 00:31:08,199
Well, we don't have money to buy lights.

375
00:31:08,783 --> 00:31:10,743
My buddy says
they throw these out every day.

376
00:31:10,827 --> 00:31:13,204
With these and the others,
we'll make our own lights.

377
00:31:13,705 --> 00:31:14,831
What do you mean "others"?

378
00:31:19,919 --> 00:31:20,920
- Dad.
- What?

379
00:31:22,922 --> 00:31:24,424
Why do I have to go in?

380
00:31:24,507 --> 00:31:26,467
I was in the army. What have you done?

381
00:31:26,551 --> 00:31:28,887
I wasn't the one who told the guy
we were gonna buy lights.

382
00:31:28,970 --> 00:31:30,889
Sometimes that's how you have to do it.

383
00:31:30,972 --> 00:31:33,141
When you jump out of a plane
without a parachute,

384
00:31:33,224 --> 00:31:34,392
you better make one or else.

385
00:31:35,435 --> 00:31:36,853
It's called a leap of faith.

386
00:31:37,478 --> 00:31:38,980
That's called a dumpster dive.

387
00:31:39,480 --> 00:31:42,692
Whatever. Get in there.
I wanna go home. It's cold. Go.

388
00:31:55,121 --> 00:31:56,164
Oh!

389
00:32:03,880 --> 00:32:08,676
<i>♪ Gotta make a move
To a town that's right for me ♪</i>

390
00:32:11,429 --> 00:32:16,601
<i>♪ Town to keep me moving
Keep me groovin' with some energy ♪</i>

391
00:32:19,020 --> 00:32:24,108
<i>♪ Well, I talk about it, talk about it
Talk about it, talk about it ♪</i>

392
00:32:27,236 --> 00:32:32,325
<i>♪ Talk about, talk about
Talk about moving… ♪</i>

393
00:32:35,328 --> 00:32:38,581
<i>♪ Won't you take me to Funkytown? ♪</i>

394
00:32:39,290 --> 00:32:41,584
- Whoo!
<i>- ♪ Won't you take me to ♪</i>

395
00:32:41,709 --> 00:32:43,544
<i>♪ Funkytown? ♪</i>

396
00:32:43,628 --> 00:32:47,256
<i>♪ Won't you take me to Funkytown? ♪</i>

397
00:32:47,340 --> 00:32:51,010
<i>♪ Won't you take me to Funkytown? ♪</i>

398
00:32:59,560 --> 00:33:00,979
I can't go to sleep.

399
00:33:03,272 --> 00:33:06,275
It was always the same way for me
after a show too.

400
00:33:07,610 --> 00:33:10,071
That's why musicians have weird hours.

401
00:33:10,154 --> 00:33:11,447
They stay up all night,

402
00:33:11,531 --> 00:33:13,700
and they only hang out
with other musicians.

403
00:33:15,076 --> 00:33:18,204
Well, other musicians don't have school.
Get some rest.

404
00:33:18,705 --> 00:33:20,915
You see what I was talking about, AB?

405
00:33:21,874 --> 00:33:23,751
Is he awake?

406
00:33:23,835 --> 00:33:24,919
I'm awake.

407
00:33:25,003 --> 00:33:27,922
We're all awake.
You guys won't stop talking.

408
00:33:28,006 --> 00:33:30,383
It's like I said.
You can't wait for a parachute.

409
00:33:30,466 --> 00:33:32,927
You have to step out of the plane.

410
00:33:33,011 --> 00:33:34,220
What plane?

411
00:33:34,303 --> 00:33:35,805
What are you telling them?

412
00:33:36,723 --> 00:33:37,723
Not a real plane, Mom.

413
00:33:37,765 --> 00:33:39,684
No one's jumping out of any plane.

414
00:33:39,767 --> 00:33:40,977
Tonight was good.

415
00:33:42,186 --> 00:33:44,605
It's all gonna be worth it, see, guys?

416
00:33:45,648 --> 00:33:46,941
So, can I get a car?

417
00:33:47,025 --> 00:33:48,526
- Shotgun!
- No fair.

418
00:33:48,609 --> 00:33:49,902
No, no car.

419
00:33:50,903 --> 00:33:51,903
Someday.

420
00:33:52,780 --> 00:33:54,198
A Mercedes convertible.

421
00:33:55,199 --> 00:33:56,492
560SL.

422
00:33:57,910 --> 00:33:59,746
The insurance would be sky-high.

423
00:33:59,829 --> 00:34:01,372
Mm. Okay.

424
00:34:01,873 --> 00:34:04,292
Go to sleep, everybody.

425
00:34:08,629 --> 00:34:10,715
The whole party smelled like peaches.

426
00:34:20,933 --> 00:34:26,689
<i>♪ Don't know when I've been so blue ♪</i>

427
00:34:26,773 --> 00:34:31,569
<i>♪ Don't know what's come over you ♪</i>

428
00:34:32,612 --> 00:34:36,824
<i>♪ You've found someone new ♪</i>

429
00:34:39,660 --> 00:34:41,245
- Mr. Larry.
