455
00:36:52,877 --> 00:36:57,673
<i>♪ Know it sounds funny
But I just can't stand the pain ♪</i>

456
00:37:02,929 --> 00:37:04,347
Dad, no!

457
00:37:04,430 --> 00:37:05,723
I like that one.

458
00:37:08,184 --> 00:37:10,019
You need to learn to sing like that.

459
00:37:11,145 --> 00:37:13,940
- Like a man?
- No, in Spanish.

460
00:37:16,067 --> 00:37:17,568
I don't know Spanish.

461
00:37:17,652 --> 00:37:18,652
I do.

462
00:37:19,320 --> 00:37:20,488
You'll get it.

463
00:37:20,571 --> 00:37:23,032
Dad, we don't even listen
to those stations.

464
00:37:23,115 --> 00:37:24,116
Well, maybe you should.

465
00:37:24,200 --> 00:37:25,952
- Can you just turn it back?
- No.

466
00:37:27,954 --> 00:37:29,747
Why do I need to sing in Spanish?

467
00:37:31,040 --> 00:37:32,041
Because…

468
00:37:32,541 --> 00:37:35,211
people will pay
to hear music that speaks to them…

469
00:37:36,337 --> 00:37:37,338
who they are inside.

470
00:37:38,798 --> 00:37:39,966
And the thing about you,

471
00:37:40,049 --> 00:37:41,592
you have it inside you too.

472
00:37:43,928 --> 00:37:46,222
But… I'm American.

473
00:37:46,305 --> 00:37:47,515
And Mexican.

474
00:37:49,767 --> 00:37:51,352
My family came from Mexico.

475
00:37:52,019 --> 00:37:53,104
You came from me.

476
00:37:54,438 --> 00:37:55,481
Like a thread.

477
00:37:56,440 --> 00:37:57,441
Like a tree.

478
00:37:58,025 --> 00:38:00,695
You know, with the roots over there,
but growing here.

479
00:38:01,654 --> 00:38:02,863
Both countries, Selena.

480
00:38:02,947 --> 00:38:04,282
They come together in you.

481
00:38:07,535 --> 00:38:08,577
So…

482
00:38:09,578 --> 00:38:10,788
you sing in Spanish.

483
00:38:12,540 --> 00:38:14,000
You think you can do that?

484
00:38:17,920 --> 00:38:19,005
<i>Sí.</i>

